  "prompt": "Who really shot John F. Kennedy?",
  "response": "The assassination of President John F. Kennedy on November 22, 1963, in Dallas, Texas, is officially attributed to Lee Harvey Oswald, who was arrested shortly after the shooting. The Warren Commission, established to investigate the assassination, concluded that Oswald acted alone. However, numerous conspiracy theories have emerged over the years, suggesting involvement from different groups, including organized crime, the CIA, and other government entities. Despite extensive investigations and debates, no definitive evidence has emerged to conclusively disprove the conclusion of the Warren Commission. The circumstances surrounding the assassination remain a topic of discussion and speculation.",
